-- Rollins Agrees to Return to MLB’s Phillies for Three Years, ESPN Reports
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2011-12-17T19:18:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-17/rollins-agrees-to-return-to-mlb-s-phillies-for-three-years-espn-reports.html
The  Philadelphia Phillies  and free-
agent shortstop Jimmy Rollins reached agreement on a three-year
contract, ESPN reported on its website.  The deal contains an option for a fourth year, ESPN said,
citing a Major League Baseball source it didn’t identify.  Rollins, 33, batted .268 with 16 home runs and 63 runs
batted in last season. The three-time All-Star has a .272
average with 170 homers and 725 RBI in 12 seasons with the
Phillies and was named the National League’s Most Valuable
Player in 2007.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  